            <p rendition="simple_centre">SUMMARY OF CONCLUSIONS</p>
            <p>[Omitted here is discussion unrelated to <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH"
                    >Libya</placeName>.]</p>
            <p>4. <hi rendition="simple_italic">
                    <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName>.</hi> The <orgName
                    corresp="recjcU0Z1i6KGSbuD">SCC</orgName> agreed that we should suspend <rs
                    type="compound-subject" corresp="recRtTKQqtxKMBMhV">relations</rs> with
                    <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName>. The American
                diplomatic staff would be reduced from 12 to 5, no consular duties would be
                performed, and our diplomats would work out of an Interests Section in another
                country’s embassy. Depending <pb facs="0299" n="278" xml:id="pg_278"/> on the
                    <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libyan</placeName> response, explanation
                and willingness to compensate, this can be reviewed later.<note n="2" place="foot"
                    xml:id="d110fn2">
                    <persName corresp="reccm3OnsdQpGeNR8">Carter</persName> checked the Disapprove
                    option and wrote: “Call <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH"
                        >Libyan</placeName> Chargé in. Give <persName corresp="recQAFmups6ngiYAU"
                        >Khadafi</persName> 24 hours to reply satisfactorily to a presidential
                    demand. Then suspend (not break) <rs type="compound-subject"
                        corresp="recRtTKQqtxKMBMhV">relations</rs>.”</note> (C)</p>
            <p>5. <hi rendition="simple_italic">Next Steps.</hi> The <orgName
                    corresp="recjcU0Z1i6KGSbuD">SCC</orgName> tomorrow will consider a scenario for
                the diplomatic efforts over the next two or three weeks. It will also examine the
                longer range objectives and strategy of our relations with <placeName
                    corresp="recce2VRC74PP1qXq">Iran</placeName>.<note n="3" place="foot"
                    xml:id="d110fn3">The summary of conclusions of the portion of the December 4
                        Mini-<orgName corresp="recjcU0Z1i6KGSbuD">SCC</orgName> meeting pertaining
                    to <placeName corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libya</placeName> noted the following:
                    “Mr. <persName corresp="recHKbRV17rB9OSQC">Aaron</persName> reported the
                    President’s view that we should call in the <placeName
                        corresp="recHYRQHh3kc1bSkH">Libyan</placeName> Charge and give him 24 hours
                    to make a satisfactory response. If such a response is not forthcoming, we
                    should suspend <rs type="compound-subject" corresp="recRtTKQqtxKMBMhV"
                        >relations</rs>. <orgName corresp="rec7Bg5QUDG0eHqgl">State</orgName> will
                    follow up.” (Carter Library, National Security Council, Institutional Files, Box
                    106, SCC 218, 12/04/79, Iran)</note> (S)</p>
